article.headline: Toledo 86, N. Illinois 83
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Keonta Howell and Florentino Valencia scored 16 points apiece to help Toledo edge out Northern Illinois 86-83 Thursday night. Justin Ingram added 15 points and five rebounds for the Rockets (15-11, 11-2 Mid-American) in a seesaw of a game that saw 16 lead changes and 16 tied scores. Toledo held Northern Illinois scoreless in the final 2:05 of the comeback win. James Hughes led all players in scoring and rebounds with 25 points and 14 boards for the Huskies (6-20, 3-10), who gave up a slim 46-43 halftime lead. Hughes was 10-of-14 from the field and 5-of-6 from the free throw line. Cody Yelder chipped in 19 points for the Huskies on 6-of-9 shooting, and Zach Pancratz added 13. Northern Illinois outrebounded Toledo 33-25 for the game but scored only seven points off turnovers, compared to the Rockets' 21.
